New Records: Victor Wembanyama scored 34 points, making 13 out of 30 shots, and had 8 rebounds.
He recorded 2 assists, 1 steal, and 2 blocks in the game.
Key Match Events: Wembanyama led the Spurs with 11 points in the third quarter, tying the game at 82-82.
He added 14 points in the fourth quarter but missed a potential game-tying free throw.
The Spurs finished the game with a 110-112 loss to the Timberwolves.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Spurs were on a four-game road trip and had a 1-3 road record before the game.
The game was significant as it was close to the end of the 2024 season.
